    "The MF subontology is usually concerned with specific molecular functions of proteins, which are more directly related to the protein's sequence, and thus the models may be more likely to capture features related to MF.",
    "If a model architecture is better at capturing localized features, it may perform better on the MF sub-ontology.",
    "the BP and CC sub-ontologies are more concerned with the biological processes in which the protein is involved and the Fmax values for ESM-1b, ProtT5, and the four comparison methods on the three datasets.",
    "cellular components in which it resides, and these functions may be more relevant to the contextual environment of the protein, its interactions, and its regulatory network.",
    "These factors are difficult to infer directly from sequence data and require models with more complex structures and longer memory to capture the location and role of proteins in biological networks."
